":"fig-pairs","caption":"Posterior pair plot. The mild negative correlation between alpha and beta is expected when the predictor is nearly (but not perfectly) centred. Sigma is nearly independent of both location parameters.","order":{"section":[4,6,3,0,0,0,0],"number":2}},{"key":"tbl-params","caption":"Parameters of simple linear regression.","order":{"section":[4,2,0,0,0,0,0],"number":1}},{"key":"sec-convergence","caption":"4.6 Convergence diagnostics","order":{"section":[4,6,0,0,0,0,0],"number":2}},{"key":"fig-marginals","caption":"Marginal posterior distributions for the three parameters. Vertical dashed lines mark the true data-generating values (α = 1.20, β = 0.08, σ = 0.25). The posteriors are well-centred on the truth.","order":{"section":[4,7,1,0,0,0,0],"number":3}}],"headings":["overview","the-model","a-running-example-litter-decomposition","sec-stan-file","anatomy-of-this-program","compiling-and-sampling","step-1-compile","step-2-prepare-the-data-list","step-3-sample","sec-convergence","the-summary-table","trace-plots","posterior-pair-plot","sec-interpret","marginal-posteriors","posterior-for-the-slope","the-regression-line-and-its-uncertainty","sec-ppc","comparison-with-lm","sec-workflow","summary","exercises","further-reading"],"options":{"chapters":true}}